Set default route 
Ip route 0.0.0.0 0.0.0.0 to IPADDR 
 send default route to area


default-information originate 




Redistribute in BGP config
redistribute ospf 1



Define bgp instance
router bgp NUM
Set neighbors 
neighbor PEERIP remote-as PEERNUM

give out networks
network IP mask SUBNET

Troubleshooting
Make sure all ports are up

If you need to set a router id for bgp, you can use an ip address since it just needs to be 4 numbers separated by periods (0.0.0.0) and unique among the network.


